# Mobile App

This directory is ready for your Xcode project. A workspace has been pre-created at the repo
root (`{{ swift_project_name }}.xcworkspace`) — open it in Xcode to see all repo files in the
file navigator alongside your Swift code.

## Set Up the Xcode Project

**Step 1 — Create the Xcode project:**

1. In Xcode: **File → New → Project**
2. Choose your template (e.g. **App** under iOS / Multiplatform)
3. Set the product name to **`{{ swift_project_name }}`**
4. When prompted for a save location, navigate into **this directory** (`apps/ios/`) and save
5. Xcode creates `apps/ios/{{ swift_project_name }}.xcodeproj`

**Step 2 — Add the project to the workspace:**

1. Open `{{ swift_project_name }}.xcworkspace` (at the repo root) in Xcode
2. In the file navigator, right-click → **Add Files to "{{ swift_project_name }}"…**
3. Select `apps/ios/{{ swift_project_name }}.xcodeproj` and click **Add**

The workspace shows the full monorepo alongside your Xcode project. Always open Xcode via
the workspace going forward, not the `.xcodeproj` directly.

## Connect to the API

The Hono REST API runs at `http://localhost:3001/api` (start it with `pnpm start`).

An **OpenAPI 3.0 spec** is served at:
```
http://localhost:3001/api/openapi.json
```

Use [Swift OpenAPI Generator](https://github.com/apple/swift-openapi-generator) to generate a
type-safe Swift client automatically from this spec:

1. In Xcode, add via **File → Add Package Dependencies**:
   - `https://github.com/apple/swift-openapi-generator` — build plugin
   - `https://github.com/apple/swift-openapi-runtime` — runtime
   - `https://github.com/apple/swift-openapi-urlsession` — URLSession transport
2. Export the spec while the API is running:
   ```bash
   pnpm --filter {{ scope }}/api openapi:export > apps/ios/openapi.json
   # or
   curl http://localhost:3001/api/openapi.json -o apps/ios/openapi.json
   ```
3. Add `openapi.json` + the pre-staged `openapi-generator-config.yaml` to your app target
4. The generator runs at build time — Xcode produces a type-safe `Client` you use directly

See the [Swift OpenAPI Generator docs](https://swiftpackageindex.com/apple/swift-openapi-generator/documentation)
for the complete setup guide.

## API Reference

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/api/health` | Health check |
| `GET` | `/api/users` | List users |
| `POST` | `/api/users` | Create user (`{ email, name? }`) |
| `GET` | `/api/openapi.json` | OpenAPI 3.0 spec |

All JSON responses use `snake_case` keys. Use `JSONDecoder.keyDecodingStrategy = .convertFromSnakeCase`
in your Swift client.
